<br>
Heck, I'd put at least the shaman, rogue and monk one as easier and many at about the same difficulty level.<br>
<br>
However, the cleric epic helps other people the MOST out of any epic.<br>
<br>
A cleric with their epic can res a 30 person raid in under half the time than 3 clerics, 2 necros and a bard.<br>
I know quite a few clerics with epics that if they walk by a corpse, they'll do a /w all and give them a res with the stick, because it takes under 20 seconds, as opposed to 3 minutes of medding if they cast the spell.<br>
<br>
Aside from that, the reason you don't see many of certain epics is because they're almost not worth the hassle.<br>
<br>
The melee epics (SK / Paladin / Warrior) are not terribly difficult to outclass by people capable of doing the quests.<br>
Two of the caster epics are complete jokes (wizard / necro) in terms of reward and difficulty.<br>
The mage epic is just plain hard, but is probably the most &quot;epic&quot; of the epics in terms of reward / difficulty.<br>
<br>
Kalli Kamerov<br>
54th Enchantress<br>
